<br>
Merciless.  Driven.  Enchanting.  Hating and hated undauntedly.<br>
<br>
At least <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>some</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of us...<br>
<br>
Our race faulters.  Our women spend their lives hopping from bed to bed, and though at least they have some aspirations, they find themselves with a child not of pure blood.  They have defiled themselves.  But I would have to say that the women, by far, are the ones with control, power, because our men seem frightened by our women, or too abused, who can say which?<br>
<br>
How they cower, bow and scrape.  How they simply accept being walked upon... it is disgusting.<br>
<br>
And those who do not cower, where do they end up?  Why... with wood elves, of course.  No challenge in the paler elves, is there?  Ah, and the romantic idea of it all, the beauty soothing the savage beast.  The darkness in love with the light.<br>
<br>
He will spend his time making excuses to sound like reasons as to why he is at all associating with an elf and not killing or corrupting her to her own demise, but he will eventually give in.  He will turn from his god, his people, who he is... and another one gives into the light.<br>
<br>
I do not need to name names, yes nameS, there are so many of you....  You all know who you are.  You who chose inferiority, you who turn away from your race, and even those of you in denial - these facts whisper in your ears even now.  It does go for both sexes of our race, but in my time in this world, far longer than my &quot;seasons&quot; will reveal, I have seen how this is considerably more prevalent in the men.<br>
<br>
You are weak, men of the Teir`Dal.<br>
<br>
And our time here, our purpose, thins with each day that passes.  The Teir`Dal do not need enemies.  Our blood grows paler of it's own accord. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>+ B R Y N V I N + S I N E S T R E +</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
