<br>
The corner of her lip twitched as her thoughts whispered 'hypocrite' while she observed him; however, after their somewhat irritating misunderstanding of one another, he had made a fairly sincere attempt to get her to meet with his House and observe for herself any answer to questions she might have had.<br>
<br>
Perhaps he had not come here to antagonize her afterall<br>
<br>
But there was not enough power in the world that could convince her that asking his thoughts on the subject would be a good idea.  Their meeting had proven how quickly something like that could lead to a sudden outburst of paranoia.  She would let him lurk, and speak up if Innoruuk gave him balls enough for voicing his thoughts on his own.<br>
<br>
She chuckled...<br>
<br>
The topic itself, however, had managed to steer slightly off course and she had done something she had made an honest attempt to avoid, she named a name.  She also realized there was little more she could say without repeating herself into exhaustion, and little point in responding to those who simply did not &quot;get it&quot; by now or conveniently did not hear half of what she was saying.<br>
<br>
It was good to know, though, that she was far from alone in her thoughts on the subject.  Others saw it, too.  Perhaps there was hope for the race yet.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>+ B R Y N V I N + S I N E S T R E +</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
