or some kind of punishment... for people just like us.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=imasu>Imasu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/23/02 10:55:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teir`Dal Men ((most likely an on-going rant))</span><hr size=1>  *He watches the hateful woman as she surveys the crowd. Smiles as he thinks of their little 'meeting'. He turns to a young Tier'Dal who has been bouncing around, attempting to gain a vantage point through the adults lingering in front of him. The priest reaches down hoisting the young boy upon his shoulders. At first the boy is terrified of the strange priest but as he gains full view of the pretty ladies, and valiant men, upon the speaking platform, he settles down. Corrino whispers to him...*<br>
 'Take note young one, these are the speakers of today. See if you will see them tomorrow.'<br>
 *A motley beggar overhears him speaking to the young one, and leans forward berating*<br>
 'What talk is this hateful one? Does Innoruuk plan to sacrifice them for their og'elendar?'<br>
 *The beggar smiles eagerly, and the priest cannot help but to laugh in his face*<br>
 'Nay you fool! They are the voices of the moment. Nothing more and nothing less.' Replies 'Then surely they are going to meet a swift ending, least their mutterings cause an uprise' The priest 'An uprising would be negative, think you?' <br>
 *The beggar, and afew other weaklings begin muttering amongst themselves. Eyeing the priest with the boy propped upon his shoulders. The boy who was staring wide eyed at the stage, fantasizing about becoming that great Knight of Hate. About earning the rights to those women. Though what he would do with them he wasn't sure, he simply knew everyone else wanted them. <br>
 Infact the boy stared so hard at the women, that the Knight of Hate was forgotten, and he slipped forward, almost losing his precarious perch upon the priest.<br>
 Corrino smiled, for he knew the boys untainted thoughts. He too could recall when he thought of lust.<br>
 The accentuating embrace of lust. A partner of fluidity, to share the moments of pure emotions. He could remember watching a womans movements, sleek as a panther, twice as sinuous. How many hours had he attempted to replicate that infernal grace!<br>
 A womans mind was so different, from a mans. Their bodies coiled with the smallest translation of desire. The ingenious tricks they used to torment, were obviously god given.<br>
 He could well understand the childs thoughts.<br>
 He used to think, that for every man there was a woman. But then, everyone is allowed to be stupid once. Once. Best you can hope for is to survive it.<br>
 Blast you Innoruuk!*<br>
 'If you beggars and cowards think that what they on stage say is heresy, then you are the ones to be sacrificed. Now begone!'<br>
 *The child snapped out of his daydreams as the priest began to speak louder. He squirmed alittle and Corrino let him down. The boy instantly darted away, into the crowd.<br>
 The priest had a small opening around him, and he took this moment to leave, glancing back only once. Looking at the heroes upon the platform, he couldn't help but to murmur...*<br>
 'And which of you will be the first to quit talking and start doing something about this plight.'<br>
 *As he turned to leave, his thoughts turned once more to what the pale one had said. With all of our infighting, what kind of kingdom have we procured. A bloody pile of rubbish. Why should any lightbearer not prey on our young...they are the more willful right now. They have won the right with our continued weakness.....for now.*<br>
<br>
